-- Oregon Coach Chip Kelly Spurns NFL to Stay With Ducks, ESPN Says
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-01-07T05:08:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-07/oregon-coach-chip-kelly-spurns-nfl-to-stay-with-ducks-espn-says.html
Chip Kelly will remain football coach
at the University of Oregon after deciding to turn down a chance
to go to the  National Football League , ESPN  reported , citing
people in the league it didn’t identify.  Kelly, 49, interviewed for job openings with the
Philadelphia Eagles and  Cleveland Browns , ESPN said. He’s
compiled a 46-7 record in four years at Oregon and reached four
straight Bowl Championship Series games.  Oregon went 12-1 this season and beat Kansas State 35-17 in
the Fiesta Bowl. Kelly’s offense ranked second in the nation,
averaging 49.5 points a game.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
